			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just got into the habit of hitting Track everytime I was stood still or just curious as to what was around me. 
<br />

<br />
I never leave my Track window open. I fire it up, take a look and close it again.
<br />

<br />
If I'm tracking a mob I open up Track, click on mob and "track", then close the Track window. Directions to the mob still appear in my main spam window. Once I find it and dispatch it, I pop Track once more, hit "Cancel" than close the window again.
<br />

<br />
It may seem a little tedious and that you're popping Track way more often than you need, but for skillups thats exactly what you want.<br />_________________<br /><image src="http://www.toogeektolive.org.uk/images/surgecrit.jpg"><BR>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660181" target="_blank" class="postlink">Surgen Sureglade - 55 Outrider of Tunare</a><BR><a href="http://www.lastfrag.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">&lt;After Image&gt;</a><BR>Vazaelle Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
