				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">maybe once I used hide but thats it...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I used Hide a LOT until just recently, and still use it every so often. When soloing and you need to med for whatever reason, Hide is an Invis that never wears off until you move. You can also do TS's and Fish while Hiding and medding. Even if we cannot Hide and Sneak at the same the same time like Rogues, Hide is a useful skill. Sneak is one I rarely used, and mostly as Kelam mentioned, to sneak up on a vendor. Both max out at such a low level that it can seem like they are useless.
<br />

<br />
If you're worried about not knowing if you are truly hidden, just create a Social Hotbutton that targets yourself;
<br />

<br />
/target (name)
<br />

<br />
As long as you are not wearing a See Invis item or buff, you will either target yourself (not hidden), or get a message stating that "you do not see anyone by that name around here" (hidden).<br />_________________<br />Bolverkr Skystrider, 61st Ranger
<br />
